The code in cell xUcv8-cowiQe is designed to find the best performing ensemble model for your employee turnover prediction task using GridSearchCV. Let me break it down for you:
model_pl = Pipeline(...): This creates a Pipeline. It first applies the data_pl (which is your ColumnTransformer for preprocessing numerical and categorical features) and then an initial LogisticRegression model. This LogisticRegression acts as a placeholder, as the actual models to be tested will come from param_grid.
np.random.seed(42): This sets a random seed to ensure that the results of models that involve randomness (like some of the ensemble methods) are reproducible.
param_grid = {'model': [...]}: This defines the grid of hyperparameters to search. In this case, it's testing different machine learning models: RandomForestClassifier, AdaBoostClassifier, BaggingClassifier, and XGBClassifier. GridSearchCV will try each of these models with the preprocessing pipeline.
gs = GridSearchCV(...): This initializes GridSearchCV:
- model_pl: The pipeline to train and evaluate.
- param_grid: The dictionary defining the models to test.
- cv=5: Specifies 5-fold cross-validation, meaning the training data will be split into 5 parts, and the model will be trained 5 times, each time using a different part for validation and the remaining for training.
- return_train_score=True: This makes sure that the training scores are also recorded, which can be useful for detecting overfitting.
- gs.fit(X_train, y_train): This is where the GridSearchCV runs. It trains and evaluates each model specified in param_grid using cross-validation on the X_train and y_train data.
- score = gs.best_estimator_.score(X_test, y_test): After finding the best model (based on cross-validation performance), this line evaluates that best model on the completely unseen X_test and y_test data to get a final - performance score.
- print('最佳預測參數', gs.best_params_): Prints the hyperparameters (in this case, the specific model) that yielded the best performance during the grid search.
- print('訓練集交叉驗證的最佳結果', gs.best_score_.round(3)): Prints the best cross-validation score achieved by the best model on the training set, rounded to three decimal places.
- print('測試集的結果', round(score, 3)): Prints the score of the best model on the test set, rounded to three decimal places.
- y_pred = gs.best_estimator_.predict(X_test): Uses the best model to make predictions on the test set.
- rint('混亂矩陣\n', confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)): Prints the confusion matrix, which provides a detailed breakdown of the model's predictions versus the actual values on the test set.
